</section>
<section id="fs-idp72584112" class="critical-thinking">
<title>Free Response</title>
<exercise id="fs-idm32376896">
<problem id="fs-idm54159216"><para id="fs-idm111434496">Describe the pathway of energy in light-dependent reactions.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-idp19136912"><label/>
<para id="fs-idp2459968">The energy is present initially as light. A photon of light hits chlorophyll, causing an electron to be energized. The free electron travels through the electron transport chain, and the energy of the electron is used to pump hydrogen ions into the thylakoid space, transferring the energy into the electrochemical gradient. The energy of the electrochemical gradient is used to power ATP synthase, and the energy is transferred into a bond in the ATP molecule. In addition, energy from another photon can be used to create a high-energy bond in the molecule NADPH.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
